British American Tobacco has called the plain packaging campaign “plain stupid”
Times photographer, James Glossop
Laura Dixon
Last updated at 12:01AM, April 26 2012
All cigarette packets should be cleared of branding, made the same colour and carry the brand name in standardised text to stop younger generations taking up smoking, a cancer charity has said. All cigarette packets should be cleared of branding, made the same colour and carry the brand name in standardised text to stop younger generations taking up smoking, a cancer charity has said.
Responding to a government consultation on whether all tobacco products should be sold in plain packing, Cancer Research UK said losing the glitz of individual packaging was key to cutting the number of young people smoking.
